text:
Yo Bhole! "The most chill and chappu guy of Y17 CSE". Bhai itna chill marke bhi kaise chaap leta hai? Abhi tak figure-out nahi kar paya mai. ðŸ˜…
Hamne kaafi college time saath ki bitaya. Mai aur Abhinav, adha time toh tere room peh aake baithe rehte theeðŸ¤£.  First year Udgosh yaad hai (Bandiyo chakar mai hospi join kiya tha)ðŸ™ƒ. 
First year Antaragni Day 1 ke baad raat bhar tere room peh GTA 5 khelna yaad rahega bro. Sikkim trip toh kaise bhul sakte hai, woh river rafting wala adventure.. It was a lifetime experience.

author: Harsh  Agarwal

text:
Dugu bhai!
"Sabse chaapu banda of IITK", and I am proud to call you bhai. I think hamari sabse pehli baat tempo book karne ke liye hui thi (first year endsem). Then TA201 team mates. Uske baad se sab kuch sath hi kiya. And tab se abhi tak we have become best of best friends. 

Teri tareef toh kya hi karu, but tera dedication is beyond praise. Itna motivation lata kahan se hai bhai? Also tera honest criticism, I love it and hate it at the same time. ðŸ˜‚ 

I also appreciate tera sab kuch share karna mere sath, tere saare secrets ya tera next move. Makes me think I am important to you. Seriously thanks for that! ðŸ˜Š

Goa trip was incomplete without you. I hope ki August wala trip ho. And I'm gonna try my best to make it happen. 

Touch mai toh rahenge hi bas Europe jaake bhul maat jana. Also, I know tu Palantir hi join karega. But I am secretly wishing for some magic, ki tu Korea aa jaye (I know I'm being selfish ðŸ˜› ) 

PS: Waiting for the first copy of your debut novel
author: Harsh  Agarwal

text:
Yo Keshav,
I still wonder "koi itna chaapu hote, itna down to earth kaise ho sakta hai", be like this always. Tere dedication ki toh kya hi tareef karu, abhi recently hi dekha, extreme circumstances mai bhi tune kaam khatam kiya. Seriously hats off for that. 

I think sabse pehle hamara baat ICPC team ke liye hue tha. Since, then we have become like best friends. Haamne itne projects peh ak sath kaam kiya hai ki hamara resume bhi almost same dikhta 
ðŸ˜… (obviously leaving the CPI). 

Goa wali trip toh hamesha yaad rahegi bro. Also, woh tera ice-cream wala incident (Hame bina puche hi tune ice-cream kha liya tha)ðŸ˜‚. Let's hope August wala trip bhi ho jaayeðŸ¤ž.

author: Harsh  Agarwal

text:
Yo bhai, 
Poore IITK mai I have known you for the longest time. And I have seen you become a better version of yourself over 5 years, following the same principles. 

Kaafi fond memories hai apni. Including Freshers dance, first year mai PHY103 ka depression (kya mast gaali dete thee haam prof ko), CSE courses ke assignment, ICPC, Nutanix (mc Suyansh) kaafi kuch sath sath hi kiya hai. How can I forget the birthday treats, tune hamesha birthday treat diya hai mujhe. I kinda feel sad ki mai tujhe kabhi treat nahi diya (hopefully sometime in future).

Goa trip mai toh alag hi maza aya. Lakin May wala plan cancel ko gaya, let's hope for AugustðŸ¤ž.

Btw, mad respect for your eagerness to go into Quantum Computing. Only few people know ki tune kitna effort maara hai. Finally, all the best for your journey at Oxford. I know tu acha hi karega. 

Baaki touch mai toh rahenge hi. Asani se bhulne nahi dunga. ðŸ˜›
 
PS: Bhai quantum wagrah toh sab theek hai, standup comedy zarur try karna lakin. I want to see you rocking the stage. ðŸ˜‡
author: Harsh  Agarwal

text:
Yo Vipul, 
Bhai tere jaisa banda nahi dekha. Tu kabhi questions puchne se darta nahi tha I like that about you. 
Hamara maximum interaction 2nd year mai hi hua... Subhajit sir ka project. it was a learning experience in itself. Kaafi ups and downs thee uss time. Tere wajha se hi mujhe courage aya woh project chorne ka. 
Bangalore mai toh kya hi maaze kiye. Woh lunch peh baate hamesha yaad rahengi. Mysore trip was amazing, I hope ki tu aur trips peh ata mere aur Gosai ke sath. But it's okay.

Hopefully touch mai rahenge!!
author: Harsh  Agarwal
